Interior Cabinet Secretary Dr. Fred Matiang’i has told security agencies to hunt down and bring to book the terrorists who killed three teachers in Wajir county earlier this month. Speaking during a tour of the Northern Kenya county, Matiang’i assured teachers and residents of their safety and urged them to co-operate with authorities to avert similar attacks in future. Matiang’i also hit out at local chiefs for allegedly mediating rape cases on cultural grounds warning administrators to cease henceforth failure to which they will be sacked. 